data.title: Sitmar Cruise Lines, circa 1960s
data.meta_description: Souvenir scarf produced for the Sitmar Cruise line, circa 1960s. It was probably made for sale in shipboard souvenir shops. This scarf is a good example of the sort of souvenirs produced by post World War Two shipping lines for the tourist and migrant trade.
